        "content": "<p>This appears to be unsupported. Using a compile_fail example such as this one:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"sd\">/// ```compile_fail</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// # use kernel::bits::genmask_u64;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// let mask = genmask_u64(0..=0);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// assert!(mask.is_none());</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// ```</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Leads to:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">$</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">all</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">compile_commands</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">json</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">scripts_gdb</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ARCH</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"n\">x86_64</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">O</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">kunit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">--</span><span class=\"n\">jobs</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">16</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n<span class=\"n\">ERROR</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"nc\">root</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;-------</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I see it's been used in macros/lib.rs, is there anything special about that crate from a build system perspective?</p>",
